      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Sometimes those hairline cracks are just houses breathing, a sign of natural settling or temperature shifts in older structures. If the cracking is confined only to the corners or near framing, it might mean your mud didn't have enough grip from the studs behind it. To prevent this, use an appropriate plaster or an acrylic caulk designed for structural gaps before applying your final coat of paint.",
      "source": "target",
